 the Chat.%0a%3c *Sanctioning%0a%3c *Listen to your Storyteller%0a%3c *During the sanctioning process, your staff member may have some suggestions for tweaking or adjusting your point spend. Don’t be offended, but instead understand that they’re thinking of you, the game, and ultimately what will make the best experience.%0a%3c *Be prepared to discuss the decisions you made for your character if you feel strongly about them.%0a%3c *Ask questions! You have your staff member one on one talking all about you, so take the opportunity to ask all the questions you may have about your character and the game.%0a%3c *See the Sanctioning Checklist for Storytellers (below) to understand what the Storyteller will be looking for.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Post-Sanctioning%0a%3c *Log out and log back in!%0a%3c *This is how you get your fancy “I’m real!” avatar in the chat. You can select your preferred chat avatar at any time from your Character Sheet.%0a%3c *Request access to Usergroups.%0a%3c *On the Forums, go to User Control Panel, then click on “Usergroups” under Options.%0a%3c *Mark the applicable Usergroup you wish to join and submit.%0a%3c *Create your Character Wiki:%0a%3c *Locate the appropriate Template, then your character’s name in the text field (replacing [Venue] Template)%0a%3c *Click “Create Wiki:”%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Fill out the Title as: Character Name - Faction%0a> Available Factions: Changeling, Mage, Mortal/+, Vampire, Werewolf%0a> Select the Group: Sanctioning %3c This is important%0a> Select Request Type: Sanction%0a> Click Submit Request%0a> Wait for your Storyteller to reach out to you.%0a> Sanctions will happen either via the Request system exclusively or via the Chat.%0a> Sanctioning%0a> Listen to your Storyteller%0a> During the sanctioning process, your staff member may have some suggestions for tweaking or adjusting your point spend. Don’t be offended, but instead understand that they’re thinking of you, the game, and ultimately what will make the best experience.%0a> Be prepared to discuss the decisions you made for your character if you feel strongly about them.%0a> Ask questions! You have your staff member one on one talking all about you, so take the opportunity to ask all the questions you may have about your character and the game.%0a> See the Sanctioning Checklist for Storytellers (below) to understand what the Storyteller will be looking for.%0a> Post-Sanctioning%0a> Log out and log back in!%0a> This is how you get your fancy “I’m real!” avatar in the chat. You can select your preferred chat avatar at any time from your Character Sheet.%0a> Request access to Usergroups.%0a> On the Forums, go to User Control Panel, then click on “Usergroups” under Options.%0a> Mark the applicable Usergroup you wish to join and submit.%0a> Create your Character Wiki:%0a> Locate the appropriate Template, then your character’s name in the text field (replacing [Venue] Template)%0a> Click “Create Wiki:”%0a> %0a91,113c82,104%0a%3c !!Sanctioning Checklist for Storytellers%0a%3c *Review the Text%0a%3c *First, read all the text, starting with the background story (after that, description, beliefs/values, equipment etc.)%0a%3c *Get a sense of who the character is as a person in the world. If that’s not clear, ask for further explanation, but keep it light.%0a%3c *What is this person’s lot in life? How can the character grow out of it? Does the character want to?%0a%3c *What drives the character? What are their wants and desires? How do they balance their desires against needs?%0a%3c *Who does the character know in the world? Family? Friends? Coworkers? Pets?%0a%3c *Weigh the concept. Is it starting-level? Does it need to be pared down/built up?%0a%3c *Review Virtue and Vice:%0a%3c *How does the character’s Virtue work?%0a%3c *How does the character’s Vice work?%0a%3c *The player should be able to provide a sentence or two describing how each functions.%0a%3c *If the character is a monster:  Has his embrace, first change or awakening been detailed?%0a%3c *Is he already part of a coterie, pack or cabal? Have his mates been sanctioned yet? What is the purpose and theme of the group?%0a%3c *Review the Stats.%0a%3c *Does the character have the dots it needs to perform its job? For example, does a cop have Firearms, Investigation, Brawl, Intimidation, etc.?%0a%3c *If they have merits with pre-requisites, does the sheet have them?%0a%3c *Are there any Banned Items? If so, the Player will need to correct prior to completing sanctioning.%0a%3c *If a character is already part of a coterie, pack or cabal, how many dots have been put in Sanctum/Haven/Totem? Are these shared dots or does the character maintain his own private space? What is the breakdown of dots between Size, Security, etc.?%0a%3c *Are rotes listed properly on the character sheet? (Arcanum X - “General name,” pg. #, Order, “Order Name”)%0a%3c *Are Public Effects listed properly? Obfuscate 1, Feet of Mist, Striking Looks, Nimbus, and other powers, merits and effects that would be noticeable.%0a%3c *Review and add any bonus points or abilities listed in the Notes section that are awarded by the purchase of other abilities or merits.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Sanctioning Checklist for Storytellers%0a> Review the Text%0a> First, read all the text, starting with the background story (after that, description, beliefs/values, equipment etc.)%0a> Get a sense of who the character is as a person in the world. If that’s not clear, ask for further explanation, but keep it light.%0a> What is this person’s lot in life? How can the character grow out of it? Does the character want to?%0a> What drives the character? What are their wants and desires? How do they balance their desires against needs?%0a> Who does the character know in the world? Family? Friends? Coworkers? Pets?%0a> Weigh the concept. Is it starting-level? Does it need to be pared down/built up?%0a> Review Virtue and Vice:%0a> How does the character’s Virtue work?%0a> How does the character’s Vice work?%0a> The player should be able to provide a sentence or two describing how each functions.%0a> If the character is a monster:%0a> Has his embrace, first change or awakening been detailed?%0a> Is he already part of a coterie, pack or cabal? Have his mates been sanctioned yet? What is the purpose and theme of the group?%0a> Review the Stats.%0a> Does the character have the dots it needs to perform its job? For example, does a cop have Firearms, Investigation, Brawl, Intimidation, etc.?%0a> If they have merits with pre-requisites, does the sheet have them?%0a> Are there any Banned Items? If so, the Player will need to correct prior to completing sanctioning.%0a> If a character is already part of a coterie, pack or cabal, how many dots have been put in Sanctum/Haven/Totem? Are these shared dots or does the character maintain his own private space? What is the breakdown of dots between Size, Security, etc.?%0a> Are rotes listed properly on the character sheet? (Arcanum X - “General name,” pg. #, Order, “Order Name”)%0a> Are Public Effects listed properly? Obfuscate 1, Feet of Mist, Striking Looks, Nimbus, and other powers, merits and effects that would be noticeable.%0a> : Review and add any bonus points or abilities listed in the Notes section that are awarded by the purchase of other abilities or merits.%0a115,122c106,111%0a%3c %0a%3c *Which area of The City do they live in? Would another be more appropriate?%0a%3c *Do they have a home and vehicle? Is it noted in their equipment?%0a%3c *Where is their home located? Is that consistent with concept and Resources?%0a%3c *Do they own a cellphone? If not, why?%0a%3c *What other equipment should they have that is missing?%0a%3c *Are the names of pack, cabal or coterie, noted on the sheet?%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Which area of The City do they live in? Would another be more appropriate?%0a> Do they have a home and vehicle? Is it noted in their equipment?%0a> Where is their home located? Is that consistent with concept and Resources?%0a> Do they own a cellphone? If not, why?%0a> What other equipment should they have that is missing?%0a> Are the names of pack, cabal or coterie, noted on the sheet?%0a124,129c113,116%0a%3c %0a%3c *Does the player have any rules questions?%0a%3c *Does the player understand how everything on their sheet works?%0a%3c *Has the player read and understood the house rules and site polices and practices?%0a%3c *Has the player joined the relevant user groups for the character? Have you approved them?%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Does the player have any rules questions?%0a> Does the player understand how everything on their sheet works?%0a> Has the player read and understood the house rules and site polices and practices?%0a> Has the player joined the relevant user groups for the character? Have you approved them?%0a131,141c118,126%0a%3c %0a%3c *Log in to the site%0a%3c *From the main Board Index, click “User Control Panel”%0a%3c *Click on the “Usergroups” tab%0a%3c *Choose the first appropriate group to apply for membership%0a%3c *Scroll to the bottom and click “Submit”%0a%3c *Repeat for each appropriate group.%0a%3c *Note that the IC forums will not appear until the applications for membership are approved by a moderator.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Sanctioning FAQ%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Log in to the site%0a> From the main Board Index, click “User Control Panel”%0a> Click on the “Usergroups” tab%0a> Choose the first appropriate group to apply for membership%0a> Scroll to the bottom and click “Submit”%0a> Repeat for each appropriate group.%0a> Note that the IC forums will not appear until the applications for membership are approved by a moderator.%0a> %0a> Sanctioning FAQ%0a144,149c129,133%0a%3c A.  Those who can sanction your sheet are as follows:%0a%3c %0a%3c *Admins%0a%3c *Story Masters%0a%3c *Narrators%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Those who can sanction your sheet are as follows:%0a> %0a> Admins%0a> Story Masters%0a> Narrators%0a152,154c136,138%0a%3c *Request Monitors%0a%3c *Admins, Story Masters, Narrators, who are in your pre-established cabals, coteries, packs, motleys, cults, etc. As well as staff that are a players friend off site.%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Request Monitors%0a> Admins, Story Masters, Narrators, who are in your pre-established cabals, coteries, packs, motleys, cults, etc. As well as staff that are a players friend off site.%0a> %0a157c141,142%0a%3c %0a---%0a> Directory: Game Reference%0a> Book Policy	House Rules	Character Creation	Sanctioning	Experience Guide	Code of Conduct	Site Policies And Practices%0a
